OL,3,CEnergy price cap to increase by 10%
OL,4,Cfrom October, Ofgem says
OL,6,FThe regulator announced it is hiking
OL,7,Fits price cap from the current #1,568
OL,8,Ffor a typical household in England,
OL,9,FScotland and Wales to #1,717, adding
OL,10,Faround #12 a month to an average bill.
OL,12,FHowever, it is around #117 cheaper
OL,13,Fthan the cap in October last year,
OL,14,Fwhich was set at #1,834.
OL,16,FOfgem said rising prices in the
OL,17,Finternational energy market, due to
OL,18,Fheightened political tensions and
OL,19,Fextreme weather events, was the main
OL,20,Fdriver behind the decision.
