OL,3,CEnergy price cap to increase by 10%
OL,4,Cfrom October, Ofgem says
OL,6,FA price cap does not mean a cap on
OL,7,Fyour total energy bill. It is a cap on
OL,8,Fhow much suppliers can charge for each
OL,9,FkWh of energy used, together with a
OL,10,Fmaximum daily standing charge.
OL,12,FYour bill will go up or down depending
OL,13,Fon how many units (i.e. how much
OL,14,Fenergy) you use.
OL,16,FThe standing charge covers the cost of
OL,17,Fsupplying your home with gas and
OL,18,Felectricity. You pay a fixed daily
OL,19,Famount for this, regardless of how
OL,20,Fmuch energy you use - and even if
OL,21,Fyou're not home.
